body.name: ASUS ROG Maximus Z790 Dark Hero (WiFi 7) LGA 1700(Intel 14th &13th&12th Gen) ATX Gaming Motherboard(PCIe 5.0x16, 5xM.2 Slots,DDR5,2X Thunderbolt 4 Ports, USB Type-C Front-Panel)

features: Intel LGA 1700 socket: Ready for Intel Core 13th Gen processors, Intel Core 12th Gen, Pentium Gold and Celeron Processors
Robust Power Solution: 20+1+2 power stages with dual ProCool II power connectors, high-quality alloy chokes, and durable capacitors to support multi-core processors
Optimized VRM Thermals: Massive heatsinks integrated with the I/O cover, joined by an L-shaped heatpipe, and connected to the power stages with high-conductivity thermal pads
Latest M.2 Support: Onboard PCIe 5.0 M.2 slot, and four PCIe 4.0 M.2 slots all with substantial cooling solutions

Abundant Connectivity: Dual Thunderbolt 4 USB Type-C ports, USB 20Gbps Type-C front-panel connector with Quick Charge 4+ up to 60W and USB Wattage Watcher, six additional USB 10Gbps ports, two PCIe 5.0 x16 SafeSlots, HDMI 2.1
body.description: ASUS ROG Maximus Z790 Dark Hero (WiFi 7) is designed for gaming enthusiasts and extreme overclockers and built to unleash the maximum performance of 13th &12th generation Intel® Core™ processors. ROG Maximus Z790 Dark Hero continues to build on the legacy of its predecessors by packing upgraded power and lightspeed connectivity under an all-new ROG ID design exterior, the latest Hero is ready to take the helm of your high-end gaming build.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Solid straight out of the box
reviews.reviewText: I was skeptical at first spending so much on this board after reading about some stability issues for stock ram speeds and ram overclocking, among the long list of cheaper alternatives, but given the features that the Apex Encore does not have, and the comparison to multiple other Z790 boards including the MSI Meg, Tomahawk, Carbon, as well as the Z790 Hero boards, the Asus ROG Strix and others that all seemed to have different quirks; I could not justify spending so much on similar tier boards. I chose this one paired with my 14900k and 96GB 6400mhz ddr5 G skill Ram. I was not disappointed, this board has been rock solid since day 1 and has not had any stability issues with my RAM and love the aesthetic. Bios flashback also came in handy during setup.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Pins came bent
reviews.reviewText: Board came with egregiously bent CPU pins out of the box, unacceptable.Seemed quite good otherwise, sturdy and a very easy-to-read manual main diagram. Testing is easy with the labelled buttons and error code LED panel. Error codes must be googled as the manual does not list or link them. Also comes with the standard support USB. Standard Asus ROG BIOS, which is one of the best I have ever used; couldn't check if it shipped with the updated version for 14th gen Intel processors. The animated screen ran ~15fps default, it looks bad. I wasn't able to load an OS to test if Asus' Amoury Crate can make it run 30/60.You likely already know if you want this board because it isn't the best value board at $600+. You are paying for ROG branding over consistent quality. To be honest, though, I am disappointed with most of the higher end brands' quality and QOL as well, so I figured I'd go with consistent ROG style.Will update review if my return processes and I get a replacement.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Looks good, has a ton of pcie and m.2, and the armory crate software is decent

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Memory doesn’t overclock
reviews.reviewText: I like the board but was disappointed that the 8000mhz memory module they say is compatible will not overclock and I am stuck at 5600 mhz. The other annoying feature is the q- lock for m.2_1 would not lock properly but the other two worked well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I'm using the AI overclocking in Armoury crate.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Waste me many time as a beginner. Nothing work but the build-in RGBs, even the Q-LED is not working properly.I like ROG products in general but the high-end motherboard qualities are poorly controlled. Returned and placed another order to see.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nothing you can expect for this money
reviews.reviewText: Ram is not able to work stable, only 5600 max, forget 8000 or you get dead screen, crashes. Nvme is not able to work on the first spot(speed drops twice down), a little faster on the others spots(a LITTLE). If you are looking to spend a lot of money and get limit your pc, because of this….

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 10, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This motherboard stuck at d6 when using dp connected to graphic card. You have to switch to hdmi for it to overcome the first boot then switch back to dp. Unexpected for a motherboard that is more expensive than 14900k.

reviews.reviewerName: Not a boomer, I'm a Xenial qweNot a boomer, I'm a Xenial qwe
reviews.reviewTitle: Pines doblados en la ranura del procesador
reviews.reviewText: Actualización: Si me hizo Amazon el reembolso así que por supuesto ya la recompré estaré actualizando de nuevo ya que llegué la nueva tarjeta madre y por supuesto este todo bien.***********************************************************************************************************************Y bueno me paso como al compañero de los estados unidos que venía con pines doblados ya la envié en devolución a amazon y estoy esperando que me den solución; arranco la primera vez y se apagó inmediatamente sin ningún pitido ni código de error, después de eso si encendía y se mantenía y funcionaban las RAM, AIO, Ventiladores en resumen la mayoría de los componentes excepto los USB, video integrado y tampoco reconoció Tarjeta gráfica discreta no puedo decir si reconocía el SSD por lo mismo, al realizar los pasos de diagnóstico del mismo fabricante me encuentro con la sorpresa de los pines del socket que honestamente cometí el error de no revisar desde que me llego y aun mirando la experiencia de a quién menciono con su review aquí mismo porque no creí que me fuera a suceder algo así pero pues esperemos que amazon sea razonable y me envié ya sea un reemplazo o me devuelva el dinero para recomprarla porque la verdad no quiero otra Motherboard que no sea ASUS ROG evidentemente soy fan y me gusta la presentación y la marca.
